Uses of Interface
MPC.Token

    • Uses of Token in MPC

      Classes in MPC that implement Token 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  TokenId
      TokenId is used to represent an identifier token found in a Pascal program.
      class  TokenInt
      Token class for integer literals of a Pascal program.
      class  TokenKey
      TokenKey is used to represent a keyword in the Pascal language as defined by the Pascal User Manual and Report.
      class  TokenOp
      Represents all operator tokens in the Pascal language that are used in OO Mini-Pascal as defined by the Extended Pascal ISO document.
      class  TokenString
      Representation of string tokens found in a Pascal program.
      Fields in MPC declared as Token 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static Token Token.EOF
      Special end of file token; convenient to make it available here
      Fields in MPC with type parameters of type Token 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      private static StringMap<Token> TokenId.idMap
      the StringMap used to hold all identifiers (and keywords), so that we can share the String (and the TokenId/TokenKey) when the name is the same
      Methods in MPC that return Token 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static Token TokenId.get(java.lang.CharSequence cs)
      Retrieves a Token given its defining string.
      static Token TokenId.get(java.lang.CharSequence cs, int hash)
      Retrieves a Token given its defining string and hash.
      Method parameters in MPC with type arguments of type Token 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      protected static void TokenKey.EnterKeywords(StringMap<Token> map)
      Enters all keywords into the table given; should be called only once.
